	"<div class=\"slide slide-24 master-content\">\n<div class=\"slide-wrapper \">\n\t\n<h1>Data Integrity</h1>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"slide-content\">\n\t<!-- slide-content -->\n\n<ul>\n<li>Each file is check-summed before it is stored in Git</li>\n<li>Every local file is referenced against this check-sum</li>\n<li>Impossible to change a file/directory without Git knowing<ul>\n<li>You can’t lose a file in transit</li>\n<li>Corrupt files won’t goes unnoticed</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- /slide-content -->\n</div>\n\t<footer>\n\t\t<span class=\"presentation-title\">Web Developer's Workflow</span>\n<span class=\"presentation-pagination\">24</span>\n\n\t</footer>\n</div>\n\n</div>",
	"<div class=\"slide slide-25 master-content\">\n<div class=\"slide-wrapper \">\n\t\n<h1>Commit Hashes</h1>\n\n\n<h2>SHA-1 Hash</h2>\n\n\n<div class=\"slide-content\">\n\t<!-- slide-content -->\n\n<ul>\n<li>40 Character string composed of hexidecimal characters ([0-9] and [a-f])</li>\n<li>Calaculated based on the contents of the files/directory structure in Git</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<pre class=\"CodeMirror CodeMirror-pre-rendered cm-s-blackboard\">1d0e85d4b9fb9bb8b0fc78009aa5817aef1b7ac2</pre>\n<ul>\n<li>You’ll see these all over the place, Git stores everything by hash </li>\n</ul>\n<!-- /slide-content -->\n</div>\n\t<footer>\n\t\t<span class=\"presentation-title\">Web Developer's Workflow</span>\n<span class=\"presentation-pagination\">25</span>\n\n\t</footer>\n</div>\n\n</div>",
