	"<div class=\"slide slide-280 master-content\">\n<div class=\"slide-wrapper \">\n\t\n<h1>Installing Sass</h1>\n\n\n<h2>Applications</h2>\n\n\n<div class=\"slide-content\">\n\t<!-- slide-content -->\n\n<p>There are many applications that’ll help you get up to speed quickly.  Most of them are paid apps.  Here are a couple:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://incident57.com/codekit/\" target=\"_blank\">CodeKit</a> (Mac only)</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://compass.kkbox.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Compass.app</a> (Mac, Windows, Linux)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/andrew/node-sass\" target=\"_blank\">node-sass</a> (Mac, Windows, Linux)</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- /slide-content -->\n</div>\n\t<footer>\n\t\t<span class=\"presentation-title\">Web Developer's Workflow</span>\n<span class=\"presentation-pagination\">280</span>\n\n\t</footer>\n</div>\n\n</div>",
	"<div class=\"slide slide-281 master-content\">\n<div class=\"slide-wrapper \">\n\t\n<h1>Installing Sass</h1>\n\n\n<h2>Compass and Ruby</h2>\n\n\n<div class=\"slide-content\">\n\t<!-- slide-content -->\n\n<p>Sass via Compass depends on Ruby</p>\n<pre class=\"CodeMirror CodeMirror-pre-rendered cm-s-blackboard\">gem install sass</pre>\n<p>or </p>\n<pre class=\"CodeMirror CodeMirror-pre-rendered cm-s-blackboard\"><span class=\"cm-builtin\">sudo</span> gem install sass</pre>\n<p>Run <code>sass -v</code> to check if it is installed correctly.</p>\n<!-- /slide-content -->\n</div>\n\t<footer>\n\t\t<span class=\"presentation-title\">Web Developer's Workflow</span>\n<span class=\"presentation-pagination\">281</span>\n\n\t</footer>\n</div>\n\n</div>",
	"<div class=\"slide slide-282 master-content\">\n<div class=\"slide-wrapper \">\n\t\n<h1>Installing Sass</h1>\n\n\n<h2>Node</h2>\n\n\n<div class=\"slide-content\">\n\t<!-- slide-content -->\n\n<p>Sass via node-sass depends on Node</p>\n<pre class=\"CodeMirror CodeMirror-pre-rendered cm-s-blackboard\"><span class=\"cm-builtin\">npm</span> install <span class=\"cm-attribute\">-g</span> node-sass</pre>\n<p>or </p>\n<pre class=\"CodeMirror CodeMirror-pre-rendered cm-s-blackboard\"><span class=\"cm-builtin\">sudo</span> <span class=\"cm-builtin\">npm</span> install <span class=\"cm-attribute\">-g</span> node-sass</pre>\n<p>Run <code>node-sass</code> to check if it is installed correctly (and see help info).</p>\n<!-- /slide-content -->\n</div>\n\t<footer>\n\t\t<span class=\"presentation-title\">Web Developer's Workflow</span>\n<span class=\"presentation-pagination\">282</span>\n\n\t</footer>\n</div>\n\n</div>",
	"<div class=\"slide slide-283 master-content\">\n<div class=\"slide-wrapper \">\n\t\n<h1>Sass is a Pre-processor</h1>\n\n\n<h2>From the command line…</h2>\n\n\n<div class=\"slide-content\">\n\t<!-- slide-content -->\n\n<p>Compile a file</p>\n<pre class=\"CodeMirror CodeMirror-pre-rendered cm-s-blackboard\"><span class=\"cm-def\">$ node</span><span class=\"cm-attribute\">-sass</span> example.scss example.css</pre>\n<p>(You can use the <code>sass</code> command if using the Ruby gem.)</p>\n<!-- /slide-content -->\n</div>\n\t<footer>\n\t\t<span class=\"presentation-title\">Web Developer's Workflow</span>\n<span class=\"presentation-pagination\">283</span>\n\n\t</footer>\n</div>\n\n</div>",
